{
  "stem": "2684.1",
  "chunk_idx": 10,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 6.1,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I can't tell you exactly the day when things happened, but I can tell you about, in my age, what time that represented, that-- that area.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And to me, the first sign were that we had to start wearing the Jewish star.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Then my parents had to give up the shops, because they couldn't have a shop in the market.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "They could have a shop outside of the market.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "They could start their own private-- they can hire or rent a-- a place.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And later on, we had to move from our home to a Jewish house.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And that's where we moved together with other families, and-- and-- and then we started being cramped up-- two, three families in-- in a two bedrooms home.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And because my parents had a poultry shop, food-wise, I didn't know hunger.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "But I know that on the street, they started looking the Jews with the-- with the David stars, and I had to wear one.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And actually, that contributed to my deportation to Germany, because the Jewish welfare agency ask for volunteers to work outside.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "Because a lot of air raids was on Budapest.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And after the air raids, you had to clean up the-- the rubbles and whatever, the air-- whatever damage the air raids caused.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "And they asked volunteers, young people.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "And-- and they gave us a-- a-- a-- a pass, which made me eligible to go out from my environment and move freely, which my parents couldn't.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "And nobody else of the Jewish could.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "So that's was the one reason I-- I went out to-- to work in this voluntary basis to clean up factories and build some roads which was destroyed by the bombardment.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "And that's where they caught me.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "And they put me on the way to Auschwitz.",
      "word_count": 9
    }
  ],
